<h1>CSC 161 Supplemental Problem 3 Grading Form</h1>

<table width="100%">
<tr>
  <th align=left width="50%">Grading Form
  <th align=left width="50%">Name:
</tr>
</table>

<p>
This grading form expands the <a href="grading-form.pdf">Program
    Style Summary and Checklist</a> that applies to all program development
    in CSC 161.
</p>

<p>
This project will be worth 25 points, based on the following rubric:
</p>

<ul>
<li>
Input:  Program reads <i>any number of characters</i> from the terminal
until the # character is encountered. (5 points)

<ul>
<li>
Uppercase letters, lowercase letters, digits, punctuation, white space read
<li>
User input can involve multiple lines
<li>
Reading stops when the # character is encountered
<li>
The program does not impose a limit on the number of characters that can be
read
</ul>

<br><br><br><br>

<li>
The program counts all letters (but no other characters) (7 points)
<ul>
<li>
Counts reflect any mix of uppercase and lowercase letters
<li>
Each letter entered is counted exactly
<li>
Non-letters are ignored
</ul>
<br><br><br><br>


<li>
Histogram is printed (7 points)
<ul>
<li>
Output starts with a maximum count of letters (not with a specified
maximum)
<li>
Asterisks are printed for each letter
<li>
The correct number of asterisks are printed for each letter
<li>
The columns of the histogram are appropriately labeled
</ul>
<br><br><br><br>


<li>
Comments on Program Format, Comments, Readability, etc.  <br>
(Points not given, but points can be deducted.)
<br><br><br>

<li>
Testing (6 points)
<ul>
<li>
Test Plan with a numbered listing of the circumstances that can reasonably
arise in this problem
<ul>
<li>
White box testing is considered
<li>
Black box testing is considered
</ul>
<br><br><br>

<li>
Listing of test cases to be considered, with the expected outcome
<br><br><br>

<li>
Listing of actual test runs
<br><br><br>

<li>
Statement of why the program is correct
<br><br><br>

</ul>
</ul>


<p>
Form updated:  20 March 2013
</p>

